1
00:00:01,167 --> 00:00:03,503
♪ <i>Oh, Mr. Tailor…</i> ♪

2
00:00:03,586 --> 00:00:07,173
["Mr. Tailor" playing]

3
00:00:08,550 --> 00:00:12,762
- <i>♪ Fix this</i> ♪
- <i>♪ Oh, Mr. Tailor…</i> ♪

4
00:00:12,846 --> 00:00:16,182
♪ <i>One cut, and it's settled</i> ♪

5
00:00:17,809 --> 00:00:19,477
[Red] <i>We can't persuade those nuns.</i>

6
00:00:19,561 --> 00:00:20,603
<i>We need to scare them.</i>

7
00:00:20,687 --> 00:00:23,481
Tonight, let's corner Sister Norma.

8
00:00:23,565 --> 00:00:26,443
[Atoy] <i>Sister Norma, I just</i>
<i>need to know something from you.</i>

9
00:00:26,526 --> 00:00:27,235
[Red] Where's the child--

10
00:00:27,318 --> 00:00:28,695
[Norma squeals]

11
00:00:28,778 --> 00:00:30,655
PREVIOUSLY

12
00:00:30,739 --> 00:00:33,199
- [music continues]
- [Atoy gasps]

13
00:00:33,283 --> 00:00:36,077
[Audrey] <i>Why do I feel this way</i>
<i>about my own child?</i>

14
00:00:36,161 --> 00:00:37,954
It's like she didn't come from me.

15
00:00:38,038 --> 00:00:39,247
[Atoy] <i>Adopt her?</i>

16
00:00:39,330 --> 00:00:43,918
Yes. Didn't you say your search
for her parents was a dead end?

17
00:00:44,002 --> 00:00:45,003
[in English] Love you!

18
00:00:45,086 --> 00:00:48,423
[Audrey] <i>I just want to apologize to you.</i>

19
00:00:48,506 --> 00:00:50,592
Ibyang gave me this.

20
00:00:50,675 --> 00:00:53,178
- Looks like you both had the same snack.
- What?!

21
00:00:53,803 --> 00:00:54,763
- Hey!
- [gasps]

22
00:00:54,846 --> 00:00:57,265
You're wasting food!

23
00:00:58,016 --> 00:00:59,517
[Audrey] <i>Oh, there's nothing wrong</i>
<i>with that, dear.</i>

24
00:00:59,601 --> 00:01:01,144
[Janine] And I don't want you
to be friends with Ibyang

25
00:01:01,227 --> 00:01:02,729
because I'm your daughter, Mommy.

26
00:01:02,812 --> 00:01:05,106
Really? You're planning to adopt her?

27
00:01:05,190 --> 00:01:07,108
Shh. Be quiet!

28
00:01:07,692 --> 00:01:08,902
[Atoy] <i>Don't tell anyone.</i>

29
00:01:08,985 --> 00:01:10,070
[Ame] <i>Hmm, all right, all right.</i>

30
00:01:10,153 --> 00:01:13,907
[Janine] <i>Help me think…</i>
<i>What can we do to her next?</i>

31
00:01:13,990 --> 00:01:15,909
[Audrey] So, it's true what Ibyang said?

32
00:01:15,992 --> 00:01:18,578
That you're the one behind
the blue paint on her face?

33
00:01:18,661 --> 00:01:21,414
[maid] Janine slipped out
through the back gate.

34
00:01:21,915 --> 00:01:23,458
What? My granddaughter ran away?

35
00:01:24,042 --> 00:01:26,669
Someone named Mrs. Santos came to me.

36
00:01:26,753 --> 00:01:30,423
Just to find and send this man to jail.

37
00:01:30,507 --> 00:01:32,050
Aldrin Galang.

38
00:01:32,133 --> 00:01:34,427
Looks like you've got a mission, Atoy.

39
00:01:34,511 --> 00:01:35,678
That's right.

40
00:01:35,762 --> 00:01:36,930
What's the look you're going for?

41
00:01:37,764 --> 00:01:38,598
This.

42
00:01:39,349 --> 00:01:41,142
This is easy.

43
00:01:41,226 --> 00:01:42,352
Wait.

44
00:01:42,936 --> 00:01:44,312
Why are you waiting on the street?

45
00:01:44,395 --> 00:01:45,563
Who are you looking for?

46
00:01:45,647 --> 00:01:46,689
A criminal.

47
00:01:49,651 --> 00:01:50,568
[music fades]

48
00:01:50,652 --> 00:01:51,528
What's up, Boss?

49
00:01:51,611 --> 00:01:53,029
You suddenly called.

50
00:01:54,697 --> 00:01:56,157
I heard something.

51
00:01:56,699 --> 00:01:58,618
That nun at the convent survived.

52
00:01:58,701 --> 00:02:00,703
The one who fell from the bell tower?

53
00:02:01,204 --> 00:02:02,747
Seems impossible!

54
00:02:02,831 --> 00:02:04,707
Well, we need to make sure.

55
00:02:04,791 --> 00:02:06,292
She recognized me.

56
00:02:06,376 --> 00:02:11,089
[Red] Tell me where you took the child
Martina left with you.

57
00:02:11,172 --> 00:02:12,799
You'll just hurt her!

58
00:02:12,882 --> 00:02:14,175
[Red] I need your answer.

59
00:02:14,259 --> 00:02:15,844
[grunts] Ouch!

60
00:02:15,927 --> 00:02:17,011
[grunts]

61
00:02:17,637 --> 00:02:18,847
[gasps]

62
00:02:19,848 --> 00:02:20,723
[Mongki] Want me to check, Boss?

63
00:02:20,807 --> 00:02:22,058
Where is she?

64
00:02:22,934 --> 00:02:24,185
I'll handle that.

65
00:02:24,727 --> 00:02:26,020
You take care of business.

66
00:02:26,104 --> 00:02:27,856
I'm short on shipment.

67
00:02:27,939 --> 00:02:29,732
We need to order new stock.

68
00:02:30,316 --> 00:02:31,276
How many, Boss?

69
00:02:31,901 --> 00:02:33,319
One is fine.

70
00:02:33,403 --> 00:02:36,364
But add more, maybe two.

71
00:02:36,447 --> 00:02:40,910
Make sure it's of good quality,
and no hassle.

72
00:02:40,994 --> 00:02:41,828
All right, Boss.

73
00:02:41,911 --> 00:02:43,913
My men and I will go around.

74
00:02:43,997 --> 00:02:44,998
When do you need it?

75
00:02:45,081 --> 00:02:47,917
If possible, before the day ends.

76
00:02:48,001 --> 00:02:49,085
Deliver straight to the warehouse.

77
00:02:49,168 --> 00:02:51,004
All right, you handle it.

78
00:02:51,087 --> 00:02:52,255
[in English] Copy, Boss.

79
00:02:52,338 --> 00:02:58,678
[suspicious music playing]

80
00:02:58,761 --> 00:02:59,929
[line rings]

81
00:03:00,013 --> 00:03:01,139
[music fades]

82
00:03:01,222 --> 00:03:03,349
Drin, are you free?

83
00:03:04,058 --> 00:03:06,019
Yes, Boss. What's the hustle?

84
00:03:06,102 --> 00:03:08,271
[Mongki on the phone]
<i>I've got a shipment to pick up.</i>

85
00:03:08,855 --> 00:03:10,189
One or two units.

86
00:03:10,273 --> 00:03:12,108
All right, Boss. We'll work on it.

87
00:03:12,191 --> 00:03:13,568
After this, I'll come to you.

88
00:03:13,651 --> 00:03:17,405
[rousing music playing]

89
00:03:18,448 --> 00:03:22,035
[ominous music playing]

90
00:03:22,118 --> 00:03:23,286
[vendor 1] Boss…

91
00:03:23,786 --> 00:03:26,331
Hmm. Boss, sorry.

92
00:03:26,414 --> 00:03:29,500
Will… Will this do for now?

93
00:03:30,043 --> 00:03:33,004
- [suspicious music playing]
- [vendor 1 gasping]

94
00:03:40,178 --> 00:03:42,430
I'll charge interest next week.

95
00:03:42,513 --> 00:03:43,348
[vendor 1] Yes.

96
00:03:43,431 --> 00:03:44,933
[whimpering] A-All right, Boss.

97
00:03:45,016 --> 00:03:46,851
Sorry again.

98
00:03:46,935 --> 00:03:47,894
Thank you.

99
00:03:47,977 --> 00:03:49,520
Thank you, Boss.

100
00:03:49,604 --> 00:03:50,897
[gasping]

101
00:03:56,236 --> 00:03:57,904
[music fades]

102
00:03:58,529 --> 00:04:00,823
Ah, Doc, thank you again.

103
00:04:00,907 --> 00:04:06,079
Just avoid scratching the rashes
or they might bruise.

104
00:04:06,663 --> 00:04:07,956
Did you hear that?

105
00:04:09,123 --> 00:04:10,208
Yes.

106
00:04:10,291 --> 00:04:11,417
I'll try.

107
00:04:11,501 --> 00:04:12,377
[Ibyang] Um…

108
00:04:12,460 --> 00:04:15,004
The medicine will lessen the itch, right?

109
00:04:15,088 --> 00:04:18,508
Yes. Pay at the cashier,
then proceed to the pharmacy.

110
00:04:19,175 --> 00:04:20,426
Thank you again.

111
00:04:20,510 --> 00:04:21,970
- [Ibyang] Thank you.
- [Ame] Let's go.

112
00:04:29,185 --> 00:04:32,313
[suspicious music playing]

113
00:04:32,397 --> 00:04:34,148
I'll buy dump--

114
00:04:34,649 --> 00:04:36,526
Dumplings. How much, boss?

115
00:04:37,026 --> 00:04:38,236
Five pieces, 20.

116
00:04:38,319 --> 00:04:40,571
- All right.
- It comes with a free… drink!

117
00:04:40,655 --> 00:04:42,240
[Emerson] Ah, okay.

118
00:04:42,323 --> 00:04:46,202
And give me the spiciest chili garlic.

119
00:04:46,995 --> 00:04:48,705
[Atoy] All right, chili garlic? Okay.

120
00:04:48,788 --> 00:04:50,498
[Emerson, in English] Okay.

121
00:04:50,999 --> 00:04:52,041
[Emerson] Mmm-hmm.

122
00:04:54,460 --> 00:04:55,503
Oh, ha.

123
00:04:56,462 --> 00:04:57,505
Is this it?

124
00:04:59,674 --> 00:05:01,134
Mmm-hmm.

125
00:05:02,635 --> 00:05:05,179
Is this the spiciest
chili garlic you have?

126
00:05:06,889 --> 00:05:09,225
Now let me taste this.

127
00:05:09,726 --> 00:05:11,894
Looks delicious. Mmm.

128
00:05:13,521 --> 00:05:16,065
[suave theme music playing]

129
00:05:36,335 --> 00:05:38,588
[music fades]

130
00:05:43,634 --> 00:05:45,136
[Emerson scoffs]

131
00:05:45,219 --> 00:05:47,180
Spicy! It's so spicy!

132
00:05:47,263 --> 00:05:49,015
- [Atoy] Son of a thread!
- This is too spicy--

133
00:05:49,098 --> 00:05:52,060
Well, you asked for spicy chili garlic.
Well, there you go!

134
00:05:55,271 --> 00:05:59,901
[sneaky music playing]

135
00:05:59,984 --> 00:06:02,153
[in English] Atoy? Is that you?

136
00:06:02,862 --> 00:06:03,905
Atoy, it is you!

137
00:06:04,489 --> 00:06:06,365
[chuckles] What's this?
Is this your new side hustle?

138
00:06:07,575 --> 00:06:09,243
Uh, wait.

139
00:06:09,327 --> 00:06:11,996
- Is this one of your secret missions?
- [Atoy] Shh! Keep it down!

140
00:06:12,080 --> 00:06:12,955
[Emerson] Hmm?

141
00:06:13,039 --> 00:06:14,165
Keep quiet.

142
00:06:14,248 --> 00:06:15,541
It's secret, remember?

143
00:06:15,625 --> 00:06:17,168
If you're noisy, they'll know.

144
00:06:17,251 --> 00:06:18,294
They'll know who we are.

145
00:06:18,377 --> 00:06:19,754
- [chuckles]
- [Atoy] Why are you laughing?

146
00:06:19,837 --> 00:06:22,507
This is exciting. [sniffs]

147
00:06:22,590 --> 00:06:23,883
All right, I'll help you.

148
00:06:23,966 --> 00:06:25,134
I'll help you out.

149
00:06:25,218 --> 00:06:26,969
What can I do?

150
00:06:27,053 --> 00:06:28,679
Um, maybe…

151
00:06:28,763 --> 00:06:31,099
I can pretend that
I'm a complaining customer…

152
00:06:31,182 --> 00:06:33,267
Or I'm a debt collector.

153
00:06:33,351 --> 00:06:35,353
Or I'm collecting debt while complaining!

154
00:06:35,436 --> 00:06:36,938
Don't make a scene.

155
00:06:37,021 --> 00:06:39,023
I'm doing surveillance here.

156
00:06:39,107 --> 00:06:41,776
- [Emerson] Huh?
- The man I'm looking for…

157
00:06:41,859 --> 00:06:43,861
He's hostile, bro.

158
00:06:43,945 --> 00:06:45,655
Where? Is he around?

159
00:06:45,738 --> 00:06:47,573
- Is he here?
- He's right behind you.

160
00:06:48,241 --> 00:06:49,909
- There?
- [Atoy] Behind you.

161
00:06:49,992 --> 00:06:50,910
[Emerson] Where?

162
00:06:52,078 --> 00:06:53,663
Behind me? Where?

163
00:06:53,746 --> 00:06:54,872
You!

164
00:06:54,956 --> 00:06:56,332
- [Emerson stammers]
- You're new here, huh.

165
00:06:56,415 --> 00:06:58,167
Boss! Uh…

166
00:06:58,251 --> 00:06:59,669
Dumplings, boss?

167
00:06:59,752 --> 00:07:00,753
[Aldrin] I don't need dumplings.

168
00:07:00,837 --> 00:07:02,547
Protection money?
Don't you have protection money?

169
00:07:03,047 --> 00:07:05,633
Uh, sorry, bossing.

170
00:07:05,716 --> 00:07:09,637
There's not much profit yet.
I'll just give you free dumplings, boss.

171
00:07:09,720 --> 00:07:11,389
I'll come back in two days.

172
00:07:11,472 --> 00:07:13,474
When I swing by,
you should have a contribution.

173
00:07:13,558 --> 00:07:15,601
Yes, boss. No problem, boss!

174
00:07:15,685 --> 00:07:18,479
[suspicious music playing]

175
00:07:18,563 --> 00:07:19,730
[Aldrin] You, yours?

176
00:07:23,651 --> 00:07:25,695
[Emerson] Hmm. I got nervous there, bro.

177
00:07:26,279 --> 00:07:28,156
He looks like… a hardcore killer!

178
00:07:28,990 --> 00:07:30,992
[cool upbeat music playing]

179
00:07:40,168 --> 00:07:42,128
Hey! What are you doing?

180
00:07:42,211 --> 00:07:44,213
Well, of course I'll go with you.
I'll be your backup!

181
00:07:44,297 --> 00:07:45,423
Backup? I don't need backup!

182
00:07:45,506 --> 00:07:46,466
What's the matter with you?

183
00:07:46,549 --> 00:07:49,051
See! I'm just trying to help,
and you're refusing!

184
00:07:49,135 --> 00:07:50,386
Come on!

185
00:07:50,470 --> 00:07:51,304
Let me help you.

186
00:07:51,387 --> 00:07:52,305
- Do you want us to be left behind?
- [grunts] Hey!

187
00:07:52,388 --> 00:07:53,890
Come on. Let's go.

188
00:07:59,103 --> 00:08:01,689
[music fades]

189
00:08:03,774 --> 00:08:06,277
- Um… Excuse me?
- Yes?

190
00:08:06,360 --> 00:08:07,904
Where is the pharmacy?

191
00:08:07,987 --> 00:08:10,781
Go straight here, then left.

192
00:08:10,865 --> 00:08:11,949
- Thank you.
- Thanks, ma'am.

193
00:08:12,033 --> 00:08:13,034
[Ame] Come on.

194
00:08:23,586 --> 00:08:25,254
- Miss.
- Yes?

195
00:08:25,338 --> 00:08:26,797
[mysterious music playing]

196
00:08:26,881 --> 00:08:29,133
Do you have a patient here who is a nun?

197
00:08:29,884 --> 00:08:31,761
Do you know the name
of the one you're looking for?

198
00:08:32,678 --> 00:08:35,723
Yes, um, it's Sister Norma. Norma Cruz.

199
00:08:35,806 --> 00:08:37,183
- Wait a moment, sir.
- [in English] Thank you.

200
00:08:37,975 --> 00:08:42,688
[suspicious music playing]

201
00:08:48,653 --> 00:08:49,737
Sir, sorry.

202
00:08:49,820 --> 00:08:53,032
But we don't have a patient
named Norma here.

203
00:08:53,115 --> 00:08:54,951
Are you hiding her from me?

204
00:08:55,034 --> 00:08:58,913
[music swells]

205
00:08:58,996 --> 00:09:00,206
[music fades]

206
00:09:00,289 --> 00:09:01,707
[Ame] Hmm, I'll check this.

207
00:09:06,003 --> 00:09:09,173
[somber music playing]

208
00:09:09,257 --> 00:09:13,094
Sister, I know what you're
going through is difficult.

209
00:09:13,678 --> 00:09:16,472
But this is the first step
toward your full recovery.

210
00:09:17,223 --> 00:09:19,183
It's also for your safety.

211
00:09:19,976 --> 00:09:22,645
We will always pray for you, Sister.

212
00:09:22,728 --> 00:09:24,272
[tense music playing]

213
00:09:25,356 --> 00:09:27,024
[nun 1] All right, I'll leave you for now.

214
00:09:27,108 --> 00:09:28,901
I'll just get your results.

215
00:09:28,985 --> 00:09:32,321
Uh, Sister, please look after
Sister Norma for now.

216
00:09:32,405 --> 00:09:34,448
- [nun 1] I'll just get her results.
- [nun 2] Yes, Sister.

217
00:09:35,616 --> 00:09:38,494
[pensive music playing]

218
00:09:39,120 --> 00:09:41,038
[Norma] This baby is so cute.

219
00:09:41,872 --> 00:09:43,708
Where are her parents?

220
00:09:44,333 --> 00:09:45,334
Um…

221
00:09:46,002 --> 00:09:47,336
[in English] Her mother is in a coma.

222
00:09:47,420 --> 00:09:51,507
And, um… it's a possibility
she won't wake up.

223
00:09:51,591 --> 00:09:55,261
That's why I'm entrusting
the child to you.

224
00:09:55,845 --> 00:09:56,971
[titters]

225
00:09:57,054 --> 00:10:00,182
But what if the mother wakes up

226
00:10:00,266 --> 00:10:02,226
and then looks for her child?

227
00:10:02,727 --> 00:10:04,770
What are the parents' names?

228
00:10:05,271 --> 00:10:06,564
[in English] I'm sorry, Sister. But I--

229
00:10:06,647 --> 00:10:08,691
[in English] I don't think you--
you have to know that.

230
00:10:08,774 --> 00:10:10,234
[inhales]

231
00:10:10,318 --> 00:10:12,111
Please take care of her.

232
00:10:12,194 --> 00:10:15,239
[in English] I'm sure
you can find a suitable home for her.

233
00:10:15,323 --> 00:10:17,241
[unsettling music playing]

234
00:10:17,325 --> 00:10:18,909
What's the baby's name?

235
00:10:19,702 --> 00:10:20,828
[Martina] Um…

236
00:10:21,996 --> 00:10:23,748
She's not registered yet.

237
00:10:24,248 --> 00:10:28,044
I was hoping…
you could also take care of that.

238
00:10:33,007 --> 00:10:34,216
Um…

239
00:10:36,260 --> 00:10:37,178
[music fades]

240
00:10:37,261 --> 00:10:39,263
I don't accept money, miss.

241
00:10:39,347 --> 00:10:40,222
[Martina] No.

242
00:10:40,306 --> 00:10:44,060
Sister, please accept it,
just for all the trouble.

243
00:10:45,061 --> 00:10:46,354
[Martina, in English] I have to go.

244
00:10:46,437 --> 00:10:47,271
[in English] Bye.

245
00:10:47,355 --> 00:10:49,565
Wait, miss! Miss, wait!

246
00:10:50,066 --> 00:10:52,234
Miss, what's your name?

247
00:10:52,318 --> 00:10:56,864
[tense music playing]

248
00:10:58,157 --> 00:10:59,742
- Sister Norma?
- [Sister Ludy] Excuse me?

249
00:10:59,825 --> 00:11:01,327
- [Red, in English] Ah-- Wait. Have you--
- [Sister Ludy] Excuse me!

250
00:11:01,410 --> 00:11:05,039
Eight years ago, my wife
gave you a two-month-old baby.

251
00:11:05,122 --> 00:11:07,458
Her name is Martina. Martina Regalia.

252
00:11:07,541 --> 00:11:08,751
Do you remember?

253
00:11:08,834 --> 00:11:10,628
Sister, do you still remember me?

254
00:11:10,711 --> 00:11:12,296
We just want to find the child.

255
00:11:12,380 --> 00:11:14,799
We want to know who adopted her.

256
00:11:16,425 --> 00:11:17,968
HOME OF TOMORROW

257
00:11:18,052 --> 00:11:18,886
[Norma] Hmm, oh, dear.

258
00:11:18,969 --> 00:11:22,473
This baby is so obedient.

259
00:11:24,350 --> 00:11:25,351
[sighs]

260
00:11:25,434 --> 00:11:29,021
I will pray that you have a good life.

261
00:11:32,066 --> 00:11:34,110
I know what I'll name you.

262
00:11:36,028 --> 00:11:37,822
Ivy Santos.

263
00:11:37,905 --> 00:11:39,532
[sentimental music playing]

264
00:11:39,615 --> 00:11:43,911
Ivy! Like my grandmother who raised me.

265
00:11:45,287 --> 00:11:48,124
I'll also give you her nickname.

266
00:11:48,916 --> 00:11:50,209
Ibyang!

267
00:11:55,756 --> 00:11:58,426
[wailing]

268
00:11:59,009 --> 00:12:00,177
[coughs]

269
00:12:00,261 --> 00:12:02,763
[breathing heavily, sobbing]

270
00:12:02,847 --> 00:12:07,726
- [glass breaking]
- [breathing heavily, sobbing]

271
00:12:07,810 --> 00:12:11,313
[dramatic music playing]

272
00:12:25,077 --> 00:12:27,455
[music fades]

273
00:12:27,538 --> 00:12:29,790
[ambulance siren wailing]

274
00:12:30,458 --> 00:12:32,251
[female staff 1] The children
will have no place to live.

275
00:12:32,334 --> 00:12:34,670
[male staff 2] We'll also lose our jobs.

276
00:12:35,713 --> 00:12:37,381
What will happen to them?

277
00:12:37,465 --> 00:12:38,424
Nothing.

278
00:12:38,507 --> 00:12:41,427
They'll just be put in another orphanage.

279
00:12:42,720 --> 00:12:44,305
- [melancholic music playing]
- [sirens wailing]

280
00:12:49,685 --> 00:12:50,895
Ibyang?

281
00:12:51,812 --> 00:12:53,522
Ibyang, what are you doing here?

282
00:12:53,606 --> 00:12:54,815
What the heck?!

283
00:12:54,899 --> 00:12:57,193
Someone's sleeping here!

284
00:12:57,276 --> 00:12:58,319
Sister Ame?!

285
00:13:00,446 --> 00:13:02,156
What are you doing here?

286
00:13:03,157 --> 00:13:05,075
I'm the one asking you that question!

287
00:13:05,159 --> 00:13:07,036
Weren't you transferred
to another orphanage?

288
00:13:07,119 --> 00:13:09,246
The people there are strict!

289
00:13:09,330 --> 00:13:10,998
And there are so many children.

290
00:13:11,081 --> 00:13:12,750
It's so chaotic!

291
00:13:12,833 --> 00:13:16,045
That's why I ran away to find you.

292
00:13:16,128 --> 00:13:18,797
Come on. I'll take you back there.

293
00:13:18,881 --> 00:13:20,674
Just bear with it.

294
00:13:20,758 --> 00:13:22,760
You don't have a choice.

295
00:13:22,843 --> 00:13:24,720
I don't want to go there.

296
00:13:24,803 --> 00:13:28,182
I'd rather be with you.

297
00:13:28,265 --> 00:13:30,434
You're the only one who's kind to me.

298
00:13:30,518 --> 00:13:33,437
I lost my job because of the fire.

299
00:13:33,979 --> 00:13:37,066
I have no savings, only debts.

300
00:13:37,691 --> 00:13:40,736
I can't give you a good life.

301
00:13:41,237 --> 00:13:43,447
That's okay.

302
00:13:43,531 --> 00:13:47,076
What's important is you're kind to me,

303
00:13:47,159 --> 00:13:48,327
and

304
00:13:48,410 --> 00:13:50,829
I want to be with you.

305
00:13:51,330 --> 00:13:54,291
Please, don't give me away.

306
00:13:55,751 --> 00:13:58,212
Um, I need to go to the CR.

307
00:13:58,295 --> 00:13:59,755
Come back, okay?

308
00:13:59,838 --> 00:14:00,839
[Ibyang] I will.

309
00:14:08,222 --> 00:14:10,474
Your situation is really hard, Ame.

310
00:14:11,183 --> 00:14:14,853
Especially since you're not
Ibyang's legal guardian.

311
00:14:14,937 --> 00:14:17,773
I understand, Sister.

312
00:14:18,357 --> 00:14:21,861
But ever since the orphanage burned down,

313
00:14:21,944 --> 00:14:25,823
Ibyang also ran away
from the place she was transferred to.

314
00:14:26,532 --> 00:14:30,244
She said the children there
didn't treat her well.

315
00:14:30,327 --> 00:14:31,871
[unsettling music playing]

316
00:14:31,954 --> 00:14:34,707
If I hadn't seen her sleeping
on the street,

317
00:14:34,790 --> 00:14:36,959
who knows what would have happened to her.

318
00:14:37,918 --> 00:14:38,836
All right.

319
00:14:39,628 --> 00:14:42,882
But sooner or later,
you need to register her,

320
00:14:42,965 --> 00:14:45,342
so you won't have problems in the future.

321
00:14:45,843 --> 00:14:49,430
Especially since all the child's records
were burned.

322
00:14:49,513 --> 00:14:52,224
Yes, Sister. I'll do all that.

323
00:14:53,058 --> 00:14:54,643
Well, for now,

324
00:14:55,185 --> 00:14:58,731
it's just me and Ibyang
that I can call family.

325
00:15:00,816 --> 00:15:03,819
It's God's blessing
that you found each other.

326
00:15:05,070 --> 00:15:06,947
Take care of her, Ame.

327
00:15:07,031 --> 00:15:08,282
Yes.

328
00:15:13,120 --> 00:15:16,749
[dramatic sting]

329
00:15:17,333 --> 00:15:18,334
This is so hard to read.

330
00:15:18,417 --> 00:15:20,210
Here, Ibyang, see if you can read it.

331
00:15:26,133 --> 00:15:28,218
You really had to ask me?

332
00:15:28,302 --> 00:15:30,846
Well, I'm only just learning to read.

333
00:15:30,930 --> 00:15:32,348
I'm sorry.

334
00:15:33,432 --> 00:15:34,350
Oh.

335
00:15:34,433 --> 00:15:36,268
I need to go to the bathroom.

336
00:15:36,352 --> 00:15:37,519
I really need to pee.

337
00:15:37,603 --> 00:15:38,646
- Okay.
- I have to go.

338
00:15:38,729 --> 00:15:40,064
Come back here.

339
00:15:40,147 --> 00:15:41,190
Come back right away.

340
00:15:41,273 --> 00:15:42,107
[Ibyang] Okay.

341
00:15:42,608 --> 00:15:43,943
[mutters]

342
00:15:44,026 --> 00:15:45,486
Miss Roma.

343
00:15:45,569 --> 00:15:46,654
I'm Audrey!

344
00:15:47,237 --> 00:15:48,948
I'm looking for Janine.

345
00:15:49,031 --> 00:15:51,951
Oh? Don't tell me you're returning
the child to me.

346
00:15:52,034 --> 00:15:53,577
My life is already fine!

347
00:15:53,661 --> 00:15:55,454
It's not like that.

348
00:15:55,537 --> 00:15:57,957
But she suddenly left the house.

349
00:15:58,040 --> 00:15:58,999
Maybe she came here

350
00:15:59,083 --> 00:16:00,626
or you saw her?

351
00:16:00,709 --> 00:16:04,129
Why would she come here?
She doesn't even like it here!

352
00:16:05,464 --> 00:16:07,549
I was just hoping.

353
00:16:08,634 --> 00:16:10,886
Uh, maybe you know where she went.

354
00:16:11,679 --> 00:16:13,806
Maybe she just went to her friend's house!

355
00:16:13,889 --> 00:16:14,932
Annoying.

356
00:16:15,015 --> 00:16:16,642
I still have to go to the market.

357
00:16:19,895 --> 00:16:23,273
[suspicious music playing]

358
00:16:23,357 --> 00:16:25,734
[line ringing]

359
00:16:25,818 --> 00:16:28,529
If you don't like me,
I dislike you even more.

360
00:16:29,154 --> 00:16:31,532
[phone ringing]

361
00:16:38,789 --> 00:16:40,457
[Janine] Don't even bother.

362
00:16:40,541 --> 00:16:42,376
Now you want to apologize to me.

363
00:16:46,005 --> 00:16:47,631
[sinister music playing]

364
00:16:48,215 --> 00:16:49,591
She looks promising.

365
00:17:03,772 --> 00:17:05,441
Emerson, you stay--

366
00:17:10,112 --> 00:17:11,739
I'm telling you if I mess up my job here…

367
00:17:11,822 --> 00:17:14,992
[phone ringing]

368
00:17:15,075 --> 00:17:16,285
Oh, whatever!

369
00:17:16,785 --> 00:17:18,746
Worry about yourself!

370
00:17:18,829 --> 00:17:20,622
[foreboding music playing]

371
00:17:27,212 --> 00:17:29,089
[Emerson] You won't mess up!

372
00:17:29,173 --> 00:17:31,216
Of course, you got me. I'm reliable!

373
00:17:31,300 --> 00:17:33,135
That's why your dad hired me,

374
00:17:33,218 --> 00:17:37,264
because I don't come up
with dumb strategies!

375
00:17:37,347 --> 00:17:38,515
I'll take care of it.

376
00:17:38,599 --> 00:17:41,518
[music swells]

377
00:17:43,729 --> 00:17:45,564
[music fades]

378
00:17:45,647 --> 00:17:49,693
[tense music playing]

379
00:17:51,195 --> 00:17:53,489
Son of a thread. They must have sensed it!

380
00:18:07,920 --> 00:18:08,921
Damn!

381
00:18:12,841 --> 00:18:14,802
[pensive music playing]

382
00:18:30,317 --> 00:18:35,614
[music fades]

383
00:18:35,697 --> 00:18:38,617
[nun] Sister Norma, do you want anything?

384
00:18:38,700 --> 00:18:40,369
Are you hungry?

385
00:18:40,452 --> 00:18:42,454
Maybe you're thirsty?

386
00:18:42,538 --> 00:18:44,832
Wait a moment.
I'll just get you some water.

387
00:18:44,915 --> 00:18:46,375
I'll be back right away.

388
00:18:48,168 --> 00:18:52,339
[pensive music playing]

389
00:19:03,100 --> 00:19:06,603
Sir, we really don't have
that patient here.

390
00:19:06,687 --> 00:19:08,105
[suspicious music playing]

391
00:19:08,188 --> 00:19:12,192
So, you're telling me
there are no nuns confined here.

392
00:19:12,776 --> 00:19:14,778
- There's no nun here, sir.
- Are you sure?

393
00:19:14,862 --> 00:19:15,821
[music fades]

394
00:19:15,904 --> 00:19:17,573
- Sister!
- Sir!

395
00:19:19,116 --> 00:19:20,117
[Red] Sister Norma.

396
00:19:20,617 --> 00:19:24,413
[music swells]

397
00:19:24,496 --> 00:19:28,709
[music fades]

398
00:19:30,002 --> 00:19:32,546
- Where did he go?
- [panting]

399
00:19:32,629 --> 00:19:34,173
[suspicious music playing]

400
00:19:34,256 --> 00:19:35,632
Oh, no, I told you… [coughs]

401
00:19:35,716 --> 00:19:37,301
she's gone.

402
00:19:37,384 --> 00:19:38,719
She's gone!

403
00:19:40,053 --> 00:19:41,722
She can't get away.

404
00:19:43,390 --> 00:19:47,561
Oh? You might blame me for that,
when I'm just helping you.

405
00:19:48,520 --> 00:19:50,314
[panting]

406
00:19:50,397 --> 00:19:51,315
Come on, come on! Let's go!

407
00:19:51,940 --> 00:19:52,774
Huh?

408
00:19:52,858 --> 00:19:53,859
- Huh?
- Come on.

409
00:19:53,942 --> 00:19:55,110
- Wait a moment.
- This way!

410
00:19:55,194 --> 00:19:56,820
Wait. I-- I need to pee.

411
00:19:56,904 --> 00:19:58,655
- I really need to pee!
- You know what?

412
00:19:58,739 --> 00:20:00,199
I'll go ahead. Just head home!

413
00:20:00,282 --> 00:20:01,575
[Emerson] Hey-- Wait, hey!

414
00:20:01,658 --> 00:20:02,910
Atoy! Wait, wait for me!

415
00:20:02,993 --> 00:20:04,161
[soft rock music playing]

416
00:20:04,244 --> 00:20:07,080
[grunts softly]

417
00:20:07,164 --> 00:20:08,624
All right. Atoy!

418
00:20:08,707 --> 00:20:10,626
Who are you with?

419
00:20:10,709 --> 00:20:11,835
Where is Sister Norma?

420
00:20:11,919 --> 00:20:13,170
Who?

421
00:20:13,253 --> 00:20:15,172
The one confined here, Sister Norma!

422
00:20:15,255 --> 00:20:18,217
I don't know anyone named Sister Norma.

423
00:20:19,384 --> 00:20:22,596
Sister, don't lie to me.

424
00:20:23,597 --> 00:20:24,806
I know you know who I'm talking about.

425
00:20:24,890 --> 00:20:27,184
You know what…
You're from the same congregation.

426
00:20:27,267 --> 00:20:28,435
I recognize those habits you're wearing!

427
00:20:28,518 --> 00:20:29,728
Where is she?!

428
00:20:29,811 --> 00:20:31,605
[nun] I don't know her!

429
00:20:31,688 --> 00:20:34,566
I don't know the Sister Norma
you're talking about!

430
00:20:35,359 --> 00:20:37,486
[Red] Can you just tell me the truth, huh?

431
00:20:37,569 --> 00:20:38,528
You're a nun--

432
00:20:38,612 --> 00:20:40,656
Hey! You're being a bad man!

433
00:20:40,739 --> 00:20:41,615
[tense music playing]

434
00:20:41,698 --> 00:20:43,492
[Ibyang] Why are you bullying a nun?

435
00:20:43,575 --> 00:20:45,327
You're in trouble.

436
00:20:45,410 --> 00:20:47,704
You'll go to hell!

437
00:20:48,413 --> 00:20:51,416
Hey, little kid! Why are you meddling?

438
00:20:52,042 --> 00:20:53,752
Didn't your parents teach you

439
00:20:53,835 --> 00:20:56,213
not to meddle in adults' conversations?!

440
00:20:56,296 --> 00:20:57,839
You have no respect!

441
00:20:57,923 --> 00:20:59,508
You're the one with no respect!

442
00:20:59,591 --> 00:21:01,176
You're the bully!

443
00:21:01,260 --> 00:21:03,303
[music fades]

444
00:21:03,387 --> 00:21:05,597
Why are you meddling?
Do you want me to pinch you, huh?!

445
00:21:05,681 --> 00:21:06,848
Oh, what, what, what?

446
00:21:06,932 --> 00:21:09,685
Oh, what, what, what? Oh, what?

447
00:21:09,768 --> 00:21:12,854
I may be a little kid, but I fight back!

448
00:21:14,064 --> 00:21:15,983
You really want me to pinch you, huh?!

449
00:21:16,692 --> 00:21:18,610
- What?!
- All right. Do it!

450
00:21:19,194 --> 00:21:20,612
[Ibyang] I'll tell my sister about you.

451
00:21:21,321 --> 00:21:22,698
She'll squash you!

452
00:21:22,781 --> 00:21:24,408
Where's your sister, huh?

453
00:21:24,491 --> 00:21:26,535
Call her. I'll tie you both together!

454
00:21:27,035 --> 00:21:29,121
You think she'll be scared of you?!

455
00:21:30,038 --> 00:21:31,248
She's big!

456
00:21:31,331 --> 00:21:32,291
Oh, she's big, you say?

457
00:21:32,374 --> 00:21:33,542
- She's gonna beat you up!
- [Red] Go ahead.

458
00:21:33,625 --> 00:21:35,669
Call her! Hurry!

459
00:21:35,752 --> 00:21:36,795
For sure!

460
00:21:36,878 --> 00:21:38,005
Stay right there!

461
00:21:38,088 --> 00:21:39,256
I'll tell her about you!

462
00:21:39,339 --> 00:21:40,257
[smirks]

463
00:21:42,676 --> 00:21:44,052
I'm not afraid of her!

464
00:21:51,893 --> 00:21:55,063
[foreboding music playing]

465
00:21:56,982 --> 00:21:58,191
[Audrey squeals]

466
00:21:58,275 --> 00:21:59,359
[music fades]

467
00:21:59,443 --> 00:22:00,360
[Audrey, in English] Oh my God!

468
00:22:00,444 --> 00:22:01,528
Oh, are you okay?

469
00:22:01,611 --> 00:22:03,155
[gasps, in English] I'm so sorry!

470
00:22:03,655 --> 00:22:06,074
[somber music playing]

471
00:22:06,158 --> 00:22:07,868
- [Audrey] Oh…
- Audrey?

472
00:22:09,119 --> 00:22:10,162
Atoy?

473
00:22:10,662 --> 00:22:13,540
[sentimental music playing]

474
00:22:19,504 --> 00:22:23,675
[music fades]

475
00:22:23,759 --> 00:22:25,010
Sis Ame!

476
00:22:25,093 --> 00:22:26,928
Come on, let's hurry!

477
00:22:27,012 --> 00:22:28,180
There's a bad man there.

478
00:22:28,263 --> 00:22:29,765
He said he would pinch me!

479
00:22:29,848 --> 00:22:31,892
Oh, what? Did he hurt you?

480
00:22:31,975 --> 00:22:33,060
No.

481
00:22:33,143 --> 00:22:34,770
But he's arrogant!

482
00:22:34,853 --> 00:22:37,272
I told him that you'll deal with him.

483
00:22:37,856 --> 00:22:40,358
I just went to the CR,
and you already got into a fight?

484
00:22:40,442 --> 00:22:42,319
He started it!

485
00:22:42,402 --> 00:22:44,446
- Come on, let's hurry.
- Huh?

486
00:22:45,030 --> 00:22:47,032
Wait. Where is he? Wait!

487
00:22:47,115 --> 00:22:49,701
[music fades]

488
00:22:51,870 --> 00:22:54,623
[phone ringing]

489
00:22:54,706 --> 00:22:59,503
[pensive music playing]

490
00:22:59,586 --> 00:23:00,420
[in English] Hello?

491
00:23:00,921 --> 00:23:02,047
Mr. Salcedo.

492
00:23:04,382 --> 00:23:05,342
[in English] Yes.

493
00:23:06,510 --> 00:23:08,553
Don't worry. I'll handle it.

494
00:23:09,179 --> 00:23:10,472
I'll settle it.

495
00:23:12,057 --> 00:23:13,100
Yes, yes.

496
00:23:13,975 --> 00:23:15,352
I'll take care of it.

497
00:23:18,522 --> 00:23:19,523
[sighs]

498
00:23:21,858 --> 00:23:23,193
Ah, there he is.

499
00:23:23,276 --> 00:23:24,319
Oh, there he is.

500
00:23:24,402 --> 00:23:25,570
That's him. There he is.

501
00:23:25,654 --> 00:23:27,864
[Ibyang] There, there. There, there.

502
00:23:27,948 --> 00:23:30,492
[Ame gasps]

503
00:23:31,076 --> 00:23:31,993
[Audrey] Um…

504
00:23:32,077 --> 00:23:33,453
[music fades]

505
00:23:34,037 --> 00:23:36,498
[Audrey] Eh, ah-- What happened to--

506
00:23:38,083 --> 00:23:38,875
What are you doing here?

507
00:23:40,877 --> 00:23:42,504
I need your help!

508
00:23:42,587 --> 00:23:44,131
Janine ran away!

509
00:23:45,006 --> 00:23:47,008
I'm sorry. I'm in a hurry!

510
00:23:47,092 --> 00:23:49,719
I-- I have work, Audrey. I need to go!

511
00:23:49,803 --> 00:23:51,012
You don't understand.

512
00:23:52,013 --> 00:23:54,182
Uh, Audrey, listen to me.

513
00:23:54,266 --> 00:23:56,518
I'll help you, okay. But not now.

514
00:23:56,601 --> 00:23:58,395
I… I… I'm chasing someone.

515
00:23:58,478 --> 00:23:59,729
This person I'm after is dangerous.

516
00:23:59,813 --> 00:24:00,689
I need to get there--

517
00:24:00,772 --> 00:24:02,190
Atoy, Janine is our child!

518
00:24:02,274 --> 00:24:04,276
[pensive music playing]

519
00:24:07,404 --> 00:24:12,492
[epic music playing]

520
00:24:22,002 --> 00:24:23,962
[tense music playing]

521
00:24:24,045 --> 00:24:24,880
What's the update on my order?

522
00:24:24,963 --> 00:24:26,256
Aldrin already has a target, Boss.

523
00:24:26,339 --> 00:24:27,674
[Red] <i>It needs to be delivered later.</i>

524
00:24:27,757 --> 00:24:28,842
Let me go!

525
00:24:28,925 --> 00:24:29,926
[groans]

526
00:24:30,010 --> 00:24:31,178
‪UP NEXT

527
00:24:31,261 --> 00:24:32,220
- [thuds, groans]
- Janine?

528
00:24:32,304 --> 00:24:34,514
Do you have a patient here who is a nun?

529
00:24:34,598 --> 00:24:36,725
Yes, but she was already
fetched by her companions.

530
00:24:36,808 --> 00:24:38,518
The nun patient is being transferred.

531
00:24:38,602 --> 00:24:39,728
Where are we going?

532
00:24:39,811 --> 00:24:41,938
[Ame] <i>We'll look for the nuns.</i>

533
00:24:42,022 --> 00:24:43,773
- [gunshots]
- No one follow!

534
00:24:43,857 --> 00:24:45,317
- [screaming]
- [woman, in English] <i>Oh my God!</i>

535
00:24:45,984 --> 00:24:50,697
[grunting, groaning]

536
00:24:50,780 --> 00:24:52,574
You're Ibyang's father, right?

537
00:24:52,657 --> 00:24:53,909
[Janine] <i>Why are you here?</i>

538
00:24:53,992 --> 00:24:55,952
Uh, there's something you need to know.

539
00:24:57,662 --> 00:25:00,874
♪ <i>One cut, and it's settled</i> ♪

540
00:25:00,957 --> 00:25:02,417
♪ <i>Fix this</i> ♪

541
